# Change Log

## Unreleased

### Added
- Backend health check endpoint at `GET /api/health`.
- Web slice test that verifies the health endpoint returns `{"status":"UP"}`.
- JPA foundation for `users` with a `UserAccount` entity, role enum, and repository.
- Postgres profile configuration in `application-postgres.properties`.
- Unit tests for `UserAccount` field initialization and profile update behavior.
- Firebase auth verification skeleton with bearer-token parsing, a verification contract, and a default unconfigured verifier.
- Unit tests covering Firebase bearer-token extraction and auth service behavior.
- HTTP auth verification endpoint at `GET /api/auth/verify` with consistent error responses.
- Controller tests for successful auth verification, missing bearer tokens, and unconfigured Firebase Admin handling.
- Protected endpoint at `GET /api/protected/profile` that returns authenticated user details.
- Service and controller tests for protected resource access and auth failure handling.
- Firebase Admin SDK integration using the official Java Admin SDK with conditional initialization.
- Firebase Admin token verifier and configuration tests.
- User sync service that creates or updates a `users` row after Firebase auth succeeds.
- Auth controller test coverage for sync invocation and `UserAccountSyncService` unit tests.
- MVC interceptor wired to guard `/api/protected/**` before controller execution.
- Protected route refactored to consume the verified Firebase principal from request attributes.
- Role-based authorization service that resolves `users` records and enforces `STAFF` access.
- Staff-only dashboard endpoint with controller and authorization tests.
- Read-only catalog module for `stalls` and `menu_items` with JPA entities, repositories, and public browse endpoints.
- Catalog service and controller tests for list and not-found behavior.
- Staff CRUD for stalls with create, update, delete, and staff-only listing endpoints.
- Validation, duplicate-stall, and staff CRUD controller/service tests.
- Staff CRUD for menu items under each stall with create, update, delete, and listing endpoints.
- Menu item duplicate-name, not-found, and staff CRUD controller/service tests.
- Opt-in demo data bootstrap runner for staff account, a sample stall, and sample menu items.
- Bootstrap runner tests for seeded and pre-existing data paths.
- Order placement module with `POST /api/orders`, order entities, and student validation rules.
- Order service and controller tests for placement, timing, and conflict checks.
- Student order history endpoint at `GET /api/orders/my` with active-order and history separation.
- Order history service and controller tests with persisted order mapping.
- Staff queue management endpoint at `GET /api/staff/orders` for active stall orders.
- Staff queue service and controller tests with queue ordering and stall validation.
- Staff order status update endpoint at `PATCH /api/staff/orders/{orderId}` with controlled state transitions.
- Order status transition and order-not-found tests for staff order updates.
- Student cancellation endpoint at `DELETE /api/orders/{orderId}` with a 15-minute cutoff before pickup.
- Staff unclaimed-order endpoint at `PATCH /api/staff/orders/{orderId}/unclaimed` with pickup grace-period checks.
- Cancellation and unclaimed-order tests covering timing rules and error responses.
- Student order detail endpoint at `GET /api/orders/{orderId}` for a single owned order.
- Order detail service and controller tests for ownership and not-found behavior.
- Staff order detail endpoint at `GET /api/staff/orders/{orderId}` with the existing staff response shape.
- Staff order detail service and controller tests for staff access and not-found behavior.
- Student order update notifications over SSE at `GET /api/orders/notifications`.
- In-memory notification hub plus tests for publish and subscribe behavior.
- Scheduled auto-marking of overdue ready orders as `UNCLAIMED`.
- Scheduler tests covering due-order processing and the empty-queue path.
- Staff queue filters for date and status on `GET /api/staff/orders`.
- Queue service and controller tests for filtered staff order searches.
- Staff reporting summary endpoint at `GET /api/staff/reporting/summary`.
- Reporting summary service and controller tests for staff counts and role checks.
- Date-range filters for `GET /api/staff/reporting/summary` via `startDate` and `endDate`.
- Reporting tests for the filtered summary path.
- Per-stall order and revenue breakdowns in the staff reporting summary.
- Reporting tests for stall-level aggregation and revenue totals.
- Order audit trail feature with `OrderAuditTrail` JPA entity and `order_audit_trail` table.
- Audit trail recording for all order status transitions (staff-initiated and system-initiated).
- Staff endpoint at `GET /api/staff/orders/{orderId}/audit` to view complete order history.
- Integration of audit logging in `StaffOrderStatusService` for manual status updates.
- Integration of audit logging in `OrderCancellationService` for student cancellations.
- Integration of audit logging in `OrderUnclaimedScheduler` for auto-transitions (system-initiated with `changedBy = null`).
- Comprehensive unit tests for `OrderAuditTrail` entity, `OrderAuditTrailService`, and response mapper.
- Unit tests for `StaffOrderAuditService` and `StaffOrderAuditController`.

### Summary
- Provides a minimal backend readiness endpoint for initial integration and verification.
- Establishes the first persistent domain model without changing the default runtime database setup.
- Adds a stable backend seam for Firebase token verification without requiring live Firebase credentials yet.
- Exposes the auth seam over HTTP so frontend/backend integration can start without weakening the error model.
- Demonstrates an actual protected route while keeping auth handling explicit and testable.
- Enables real Firebase Admin token verification when configured, while keeping the app safe to run without credentials.
- Keeps the user record in sync with Firebase identity data without changing the existing auth response format.
- Moves auth enforcement into the MVC layer so protected routes are guarded consistently.
- Adds a minimal role-based access path for staff accounts without mixing authorization into token verification.
- Starts the actual canteen domain model in a stable, read-only form for frontend menu browsing.
- Adds the first staff-managed write path for the canteen domain without changing menu-item behavior yet.
- Extends staff management to the menu layer so stalls can now own editable item catalogs.
- Gives the app a predictable demo dataset without enabling auto-seeding in normal runs.
- Adds the first checkout flow so students can submit orders against a stall catalog.
- Gives students visibility into current active orders and past order history.
- Gives staff a live queue view for incoming and in-progress orders by stall.
- Lets staff move an order through the kitchen lifecycle without bypassing the existing auth model.
- Gives students a controlled way to cancel pending orders before the pickup cutoff.
- Lets staff mark late, unclaimed ready orders so the queue reflects the real pickup state.
- Lets students open one owned order directly instead of only using the list view.
- Lets staff open a single order directly from the queue or any other staff workflow.
- Lets students receive status-change updates without polling the order history endpoint.
- Automatically keeps overdue ready orders moving into the unclaimed state without manual staff action.
- Lets staff narrow the queue to a specific date or order status without changing the existing endpoint shape.
- Gives staff a compact operational snapshot without adding a separate reporting table or job.
- Lets staff narrow the operational summary to a specific date span without changing the payload shape.
- Lets staff see which stalls are driving orders and revenue inside the same summary endpoint.

### Updated
- Moved the Spring Boot backend project files into `backend/`.
- Moved the project context files into `CanteenQ/Context/` and added a placeholder file to keep the folder explicit.
